notesStmt.note: First back flyleaf is the last folio in the last quire

msContents.summary: This fifteenth-century French manuscript contains two texts by Saint Bonaventure.

msItem.title: Meditationes super Genesim; Novella materia super septem peccatis capitalibus
msItem.author: Bonaventure, Saint, Cardinal, approximately 1217-1274

supportDesc.extent: ii+161+ii; 105 x 73 mm bound to 109 x 78 mm

p.signatures: First four leaves of every quire numbered 1, 2, 3, 4; bottom right recto

layoutDesc.layout: One column of 19 lines; frame-ruled in pencil or light ink; written area: 82 x 50 mm

decoDesc.decoNote: Three-line red initial P (fol. 1r); Red three-line initial M (fol. 117r); red two-line initials and rubrication throughout

binding.p: Original wood boards, stamped calf, remains of a metal clasp

origin.p: Written in the monaster of the Blessed Virgin of the Celestine Order at Metz, France, by Frater Johannes clericus; 15th century

history.provenance: Was number 0/88/ in the monastery library; owned in 1517 by Count Villiers de Boterhan
